originalText.text: After explaining CLEARLY that I had no money to spend, Megan assured me the $300 free ads would help. It didn't, because it was a scam. I'm out $124.45...it's a shame. Yelp has the staff & presence to actually help people...but instead they prey on small businesses. Stay away from Yelp... don't use their app...tell other businesses not to use them. Calling my State Attorney General next week. I contacted the Better Business Bureau already. Yelp, you have the staff...you have the web space.... WHY DO YOU SCAM when you could actually help businesses grow & they would be LOYAL to you???

originalText.text: Yelp has the worst review filtering system. It stifles new companies from being able to get reviews by needlessly hiding legitimate reviews because of some algorithm they claim to have no control over. Don't waste your money with them.

originalText.text: Pretty Terrible company for a company that focuses on customer reviews. I use their business platform and pay almost $300 a month and get very little in return. You can’t cancel online. I called to cancel and it was past business hours. I emailed and they said they would call back in 3 business days. It’s been almost ten days and I still have not received a call.

They will also harass you to create an account. The customer service guy would not let me talk. I strongly advise not to do anything with this platform.
